{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = SOLAS |type = Executive Agency |logo = |formed = {{start date and age|2013|10|27}} |preceding1 = [[Foras Áiseanna Saothair]] |jurisdiction = [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] |headquarters = Castleforbes Road, [[Dublin]] |parent_department = [[Department of Education and Skills (Ireland)|Department of Education and Skills]] |website = {{URL|solas.ie}} }}
'''SOLAS''' ({{lang-ga|An tSeirbhís Oideachais Leanúnaigh agus Scileanna|lit=Further Education and Skills Service}}) is a [[Public service bodies of the Republic of Ireland|state agency]] in Ireland. SOLAS was established on {{start date|2013|10|27}}. Its mandate is set out in the Further Education and Training Act 2013. Among other functions such as research, monitoring and co-ordinating of further education and training provision,<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-10-26|title=A lot done in further education ... more to do|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/education/a-lot-done-in-further-education-more-to-do-1.1925529?mode=sample&auth-failed=1&pw-origin=https%253A%252F%252Fwww.irishtimes.com%252Fnews%252Feducation%252Fa-lot-done-in-further-education-more-to-do-1.1925529|newspaper=The Irish Times}}</ref> it also advances moneys to education and training boards and other bodies engaged in the provision of further education and training programmes.
The sixteen education and training boards (ETBs) were established on the dissolution of the 33 Vocational Education Committees (VECs).<ref name="irishtimes-2013">{{cite news|accessdate=2018-10-26|title=If Solas is the new FÁS, can it make a difference?|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/education/if-solas-is-the-new-f%25C3%25A1s-can-it-make-a-difference-1.1253198|newspaper=The Irish Times}}</ref> At about the same time FAS, the national training and employment authority established in 1987, was also dissolved.<ref name="irishtimes-2013"/> The [[Department of Social Protection]] took over the responsibility from FÁS for Community Employment and Employment Services and over 800 former FAS staff. In 2014 the transfer of the former FAS training centre network, its 600+ staff and training facilities to the newly established education and training boards was successfully completed.
ETBs grant aided by SOLAS, offer around 270,000 places on 20,000+ further education and training courses in any one year. SOLAS also administers the Irish apprenticeship system.<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-10-26|title=Thousands opt for further education programmes, apprenticeships, traineeships|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/education/thousands-opt-for-further-education-programmes-apprenticeships-traineeships-1.3601982|newspaper=The Irish Times}}</ref> SOLAS publishes an annual services plan setting out what further education and training courses will be provided in the sixteen ETBs in any one year and how much these courses will cost.
